{
  "doc_id": "59467",
  "text": "Performance of a TOE in patients who are in sinus rhythm at the time of ablation or correctly treated by anticoagulants is not mandatory but is considered a useful additional precaution. [CITATION_1] Pre-procedure contrast-injected CT or CMR is used in many centres in order to evaluate LA and pulmonary veins size and anatomy with precision. These image sets are then used for anatomical guidance during the procedure.",
  "correct_citation": {
