      "span_text": "Performance of a TOE in patients who are in sinus rhythm at the time of ablation or correctly treated by anticoagulants is not mandatory but is considered a useful additional precaution. Pre-procedure contrast-injected CT or CMR is used in many centres in order to evaluate LA and pulmonary veins size and anatomy with precision."
